fields.description:
When viewing the branch page anonymously on a public repository the ahead and behind information is not loaded and a warning is added to the logs. 

Example warning:
{code}
c.a.s.i.r.PluginRefMetadataMapProvider Failed to retrieve ref metadata for com.atlassian.stash.stash-branch-utils:ahead-behind-metadata-provider
org.springframework.security.authentication.AuthenticationCredentialsNotFoundException: An Authentication object was not found in the SecurityContext
{code}

Creating on behalf of customer:
{quote}
API call to be able to change the repository settings regarding pull requests. When a pull request is created, you cannot change the number of approvers nor the number of successful builds needed for merge to happen. (At present) These options can only be set under the repository settings tabs, under the pull request section (via the UI).
{quote}

{noformat}
2013-10-04 01:11:57,400 WARN  [scheduler_Worker-6]  o.h.internal.AbstractQueryImpl HHH000443: Dialect [org.hibernate.dialect.Oracle10gDialect] limits the number of elements in an IN predicate to 1000 entries.  However, the given parameter list [usernames] contained 2000 entries, which will likely cause failures to execute the query in the database
2013-10-04 01:11:57,408 WARN  [scheduler_Worker-6]  o.h.e.jdbc.spi.SqlExceptionHelper SQL Error: 1795, SQLState: 42000
2013-10-04 01:11:57,409 ERROR [scheduler_Worker-6]  o.h.e.jdbc.spi.SqlExceptionHelper ORA-01795: maximum number of expressions in a list is 1000
{noformat}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Pistachios.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
Clone button inconsistency with bitbucket - bitbucket prepend "git clone " for easy copy-pasta into the terminal, and stash does not.
{panel}

Steps to reproduce:

1. Create pull request.
2. Add the following comment:
{quote}
```<table>```
{quote}
3. In preview you will see:
{quote}
<table class="aui">
{quote}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Overall the tutorial was well done and provided me with some of the basics.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
There are some mistakes in some of the steps.

In the Prepare your project and delete boilerplate code section the paths are not correct and the first two files didn't exist so I didn't have to delete them.

In the sample implementations the package name isn't used consistently.  In some areas it's com.atlassian.stash.pull.merge.checks in others it's com.mycompany.stash.pull.merge.checks and in some cases it's com.mycompany.stash.merge.checks.  This prevents the plugin from being enabled.

{panel}

*Reporter*: Steven Whitman
*E-mail*: [mailto:stevew@cognex.com]

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
Pull requests
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
When your diff has changes in one continuous chunk, there's no 'Show More' text on the tear lines. I couldn't figure out how to get more context until I asked someone.
{panel}

Currently the DB accepts up to 255 char but the UI doesn't show them, instead it will truncate the text following this CSS rule:
{code}
text-overflow: ellipsis; 
{code}

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
I want a way to be able to see the activity of a user, their commits etc.
{panel}
